import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="ticks")
    g = sns.FacetGrid(data, col="Series", hue="Series", col_wrap=2, height=4)
    g.map(sns.scatterplot, "X", "Y", alpha=.7)
    g.set_axis_labels("X", "Y")
    g.fig.subplots_adjust(top=0.9)
    g.fig.suptitle("What is the relationship between X and Y values in each series?")
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Y', hue='Series', multiple='stack', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['Y'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Y values across all series?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Series'] = data['Series'].astype('category')
    sns.set(style="ticks")
    g = sns.FacetGrid(data, col="Series", hue="Series", col_wrap=2)
    g.map(sns.scatterplot, "X", "Y", alpha=.7)
    g.set_axis_labels("X", "Y")
    g.fig.suptitle("What is the correlation between X and Y values across all series?", y=1.05)
    plt.subplots_adjust(top=0.85)
    plt.show()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['X-Y'] = data['X'] - data['Y']
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='X-Y', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(x=data['X-Y'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(x=data['X-Y'].median(), color='green', linestyle='--', label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the difference between X and Y values across all series?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('X-Y')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
